<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-02T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-02T10:00:00-05:00" n="202" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d202">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3898: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-02T23:00:00+08:00">February 2, 1932—11
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received February 3—2:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your 12, February 1, 3 p.m. [to Peck.] I arrived Nanking this afternoon
                            and saw Minister of Foreign Affairs 5 o’clock to whom
                                <persName>Peck</persName> had just delivered Department’s
                            message.</p>
                        <p><persName corresp="#p_LW1">Lo</persName> showed me fragments of shells
                            which he stated had fallen on Lion Hill and on Pei Chi Ko where
                                <persName corresp="#p_STV1">Soong</persName> has house.</p>
                        <p>Saw <persName corresp="#p_STV1">Soong</persName> this evening. He said
                            American note gives them hope although he does not believe Japanese will
                            accept. He expects to go to Shanghai tomorrow to persuade bankers to
                            give him money.</p>
                        <p>French Minister received his instruction about 8 p.m.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_JNT1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>